W W Grainger Inc (GWW) Position Increased by HM Payson & Co.

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 

HM Payson & Co. increased its position in shares of W W Grainger Inc (NYSE:GWW) by 14.1% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor owned 1,622 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after buying an additional 200 shares during the period. HM Payson & Co.’s holdings in W W Grainger were worth $377,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
A number of other hedge funds also recently modified their holdings of the stock. Federated Investors Inc. PA raised its position in shares of W W Grainger by 46.4% in the fourth quarter. Federated Investors Inc. PA now owns 2,334 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $542,000 after buying an additional 740 shares during the period. FMR LLC raised its position in shares of W W Grainger by 11.5% in the fourth quarter. FMR LLC now owns 183,047 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $42,512,000 after buying an additional 18,937 shares during the period. Marshall Wace LLP purchased a new position in shares of W W Grainger during the fourth quarter worth $671,000. Thrivent Financial for Lutherans increased its position in shares of W W Grainger by 5.4% in the fourth quarter. Thrivent Financial for Lutherans now owns 1,950 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $453,000 after buying an additional 100 shares in the last quarter. Finally, Numeric Investors LLC increased its position in shares of W W Grainger by 26.9% in the fourth quarter. Numeric Investors LLC now owns 6,600 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $1,533,000 after buying an additional 1,400 shares in the last quarter. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own 79.75% of the company’s stock. 


 Get W W Grainger Inc alerts:



Shares of W W Grainger Inc (NYSE:GWW) opened at 164.94 on Friday. W W Grainger Inc has a 12 month low of $160.29 and a 12 month high of $262.71. The stock has a market cap of $9.63 billion, a PE ratio of 16.84 and a beta of 0.76. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $175.27 and its 200 day moving average is $213.21. 




W W Grainger (NYSE:GWW) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Wednesday, July 19th. The industrial products company reported $2.74 earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $2.65 by $0.09. W W Grainger had a net margin of 4.09% and a return on equity of 21.42%. The company had revenue of $2.62 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $2.63 billion. During the same quarter in the prior year, the company earned $2.89 EPS. W W Grainger’s quarterly revenue was up 2.0% on a year-over-year basis. On average, equities analysts predict that W W Grainger Inc will post $10.38 EPS for the current year. 
