HM Payson & Co. Has $216,000 Position in Hubbell Inc (HUBB)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments 

HM Payson & Co. continued to hold its position in Hubbell Inc (NYSE:HUBB) during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor owned 1,800 shares of the industrial products company’s stock at the end of the first quarter. HM Payson & Co.’s holdings in Hubbell were worth $216,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Several other large investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in HUBB. Pointe Capital Management LLC purchased a new stake in Hubbell during the first quarter valued at about $279,000. Janus Capital Management LLC raised its stake in shares of Hubbell by 204.9% in the first quarter. Janus Capital Management LLC now owns 62,800 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $7,539,000 after buying an additional 42,200 shares during the period. Credit Suisse AG raised its stake in shares of Hubbell by 1.5% in the first quarter. Credit Suisse AG now owns 285,034 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $34,220,000 after buying an additional 4,305 shares during the period. Tudor Investment Corp ET AL raised its stake in shares of Hubbell by 16.9% in the first quarter. Tudor Investment Corp ET AL now owns 79,391 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $9,531,000 after buying an additional 11,498 shares during the period. Finally, Westwood Holdings Group Inc. raised its stake in shares of Hubbell by 7.5% in the first quarter. Westwood Holdings Group Inc. now owns 491,140 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $58,962,000 after buying an additional 34,258 shares during the period. 85.31% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Hubbell Inc alerts:



Shares of Hubbell Inc (NYSE:HUBB) traded down 0.88% during trading on Friday, hitting $116.12. The stock had a trading volume of 418,936 shares. The company’s 50 day moving average price is $115.60 and its 200 day moving average price is $117.66. The stock has a market cap of $6.39 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 21.93 and a beta of 1.01. Hubbell Inc has a 12 month low of $101.15 and a 12 month high of $125.93. 




Hubbell (NYSE:HUBB) last announced its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, April 25th. The industrial products company reported $1.23 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $1.11 by $0.12. The firm had revenue of $852.30 million during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $848.70 million. Hubbell had a return on equity of 19.96% and a net margin of 8.37%. Hubbell’s quarterly revenue was up 2.1% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period in the previous year, the company earned $1.16 earnings per share. Equities research analysts expect that Hubbell Inc will post $5.48 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
